{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/niocore\/channeloptions\/types\/datagramvectorreadmessagecountoption"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/NIOCore","doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/NIOCore\/ChannelOptions","doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/NIOCore\/ChannelOptions\/Types"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DatagramVectorReadMessageCountOption"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some datagram ","type":"text"},{"code":"Channel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s have extremely high datagram throughput. This can occur when the single datagram socket is encapsulating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many logical “connections” (e.g. with QUIC) or when the datagram socket is simply serving an enormous number of consumers (e.g.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a public-facing DNS server). In this case the overhead of one syscall per datagram is profoundly limiting. Using this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ChannelOption","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" allows the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Channel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to read multiple datagrams at once.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that simply increasing this number will not necessarily bring performance gains and may in fact cause data loss. Any increase","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to this should be matched by increasing the size of the buffers allocated by the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Channel"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecvByteBufferAllocator"},{"text":" (as set by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ChannelOption.recvAllocator"},{"text":") proportionally. For example, to receive 10 messages at a time, set the size of the buffers allocated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecvByteBufferAllocator"},{"text":" to at least 10x the size of the maximum datagram size you wish to receive.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Naturally, this option is only valid on datagram channels."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This option only works on the following platforms:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Linux","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"FreeBSD","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Android"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On all other platforms, setting it has no effect.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set this option to 0 to disable vector reads and to use serial reads instead."}]}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/NIOCore\/ChannelOption","doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/documentation\/NIOCore\/NIOPreconcurrencySendable","doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/SQ","doc:\/\/co.pointfree.VaporRouting\/s8SendableP"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DatagramVectorReadMessageCountOption"},{"text":" allows users to configure the number of messages to attempt to read in a single syscall on a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"datagram ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Channel"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind"